  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">CF Amalia sub-debt Colombia</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The development impact of IFC&apos;&apos;s investment in this Project is expected to be high given that:   - The Project would enable greater cross-border financial integration in LAC, as it would assist the Bank to consolidate its presence in a new market.  By becoming a regional player and a systemic bank in the Country, the Bank and its Sponsor would be (a) promoting commercial trade between two or more countries; b) supporting the increasing trend of companies setting operations and expanding regionally, and (c) improving institutions and investment climate through higher ESG standards. - The proposed transaction would support the creation of a financial services platform with deep roots in LAC. This is expected to diminish the volatility derived from large international investors entering and exiting developing markets. Clients will gain additional confidence in the banking system leading to overall increased economic stability.   - One of the Bank&apos;&apos;s strategic objectives is to continue focusing on the SME business, as the majority&apos;&apos;s of the Country&apos;&apos;s total SMEs lack adequate access to bank financing.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project involves a Subordinated Bond issued by Banco Corpbanca Colombia S.A. (the Bank) to be subscribed in part or in whole by IFC and the IFC Capitalization Fund, LP. The purpose of the proposed investment is to support the Banks growth plans in Colombia.</narrative>
  </description>
